message.content:
1. The cleavage and blastocyst rates were lower in the Vitrified group.
2. The difference in rates between the Vitrified group and the Control, VS1 and VS1 + VS2 groups was statistically significant (P < 0.001).
3. In Experiment 1, the cleavage and blastocyst rates in the Vitrified group were 40.9% and 1.6% respectively.
4. In Experiment 1, the cleavage and blastocyst rates in the Control group were 92.2% and 34.4% respectively.
5. In Experiment 1, the cleavage and blastocyst rates in the VS1 group were 79.4% and 25.2% respectively.
6. In Experiment 1, the cleavage and blastocyst rates in the VS1 + VS2 group were 80.2% and 20.8% respectively.
7. In Experiment 2, the cleavage and blastocyst rates in the Vitrified group were 25.0% and 1.7% respectively.
8. In Experiment 2, the cleavage and blastocyst rates in the Control group were 75.3% and 27.2% respectively.
9. In Experiment 2, the cleavage and blastocyst rates in the VS1 group were 67.9% and 19.5% respectively.
10. In Experiment 2, the cleavage and blastocyst rates in the VS1 + VS2 group were 62.7% and 22.5% respectively.

messages.content:
Statement: However, both cleavage and blastocyst rates were lower (P < 0.001) in the Vitrified group than in the Control, VS1 and VS1 + VS2 groups (40.9 and 1.6% vs 92.2 and 34.4%, 79.4 and 25.2%, and 80.2 and 20.8%, respectively in Experiment 1, and 25.0 and 1.7% vs 75.3 and 27.2%, 67.9 and 19.5%, and 62.7 and 22.5%, respectively in Experiment 2).
